# FastAPI — Project Conventions

This is the **FastAPI** backend in the Tripteki parallel-codebase family. It is structurally parallel to the NestJS codebase and shares the same API contract with Laravel.

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | FastAPI 0.115 + Python 3.10+ |
| Package manager | **Poetry** (`package-mode = false`) |
| ORM | SQLModel + Alembic (PostgreSQL) + Motor (MongoDB) |
| Cache/Queue | Redis — cache, RQ job queues, FastAPI-Limiter |
| REST | Swagger at `/api/docs` (auto-generated) |
| GraphQL | Strawberry at `/graphql` |
| WebSockets | python-socketio — room-based emits to `user.{id}` |
| Auth | JWT via python-jose — access + refresh tokens |
| Mail | Jinja2 templates |
| Scheduler | APScheduler |
| Limiter | FastAPI-Limiter (production only) |

## Directory layout

```
main.py                         # App entry + lifespan context manager
cli.py                          # Thin wrapper → src/cli.py
src/
  cli.py                        # CLI commands (migrate, queue, seed, etc.)
  app/                          # Infrastructure layer
    bases/                      # Base classes (AppConfig, AppRealtime, etc.)
    configs/                    # Config classes extending AppConfig
    routes/                     # Router registration (app_ws_router.py)
    dependencies/               # FastAPI Depends() providers
    exceptions/                 # Custom exception handlers
    databases/
      migrations/               # Alembic migrations
  v1/
    api/{domain}/               # REST domain modules
      controllers/
      services/
      repositories/
      dtos/                     # validator, transformer
      events/                   # Nested: events/user/auth/registered/event.py
      listeners/
      processors/               # RQ queue processors
      databases/models/
      consoles/commands/
    graphql/{domain}/           # Strawberry resolvers
test/
  conftest.py                   # Fixtures (patches FastAPILimiter Redis)
  helpers.py                    # Test utilities
  v1/                           # Domain tests (test_user.py, test_notification.py)
  test_status.py
storage/logs/
storage/disks/{public,private}/
```

## Naming conventions

| Artifact | Convention | Example |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| File | snake_case | `user_auth_service.py` |
| Class | PascalCase | `UserAuthService` |
| Method | camelCase + space after `(` | `def validateToken (self, token: str)` |
| Event dir | nested path | `events/user/auth/registered/event.py` |
| Validator DTO | `*_validator_dto.py` | `user_validator_dto.py` |
| Transformer DTO | `*_transformer_dto.py` | `user_transformer_dto.py` |

Note the project-wide style: **space after opening parenthesis** in function definitions.

## Shared API contract (all backends)

### Endpoints
- REST base: `/api/v1`
- Swagger docs: `/api/docs`
- GraphQL: `/graphql`

### Auth
- `POST /api/v1/auth/login` — `{ access_token, refresh_token, token_type, expires_in }`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/refresh`, `POST /api/v1/auth/register`, `POST /api/v1/auth/logout`
- `GET /api/v1/auth/profile`
- Login supports `remember` flag

### Error responses
```json
// Validation (HTTP 422)
{ "detail": [{ "loc": ["body", "email"], "msg": "...", "type": "..." }] }

// General
{ "message": "Human-readable error" }
```

### Pagination
```json
{ "data": [...], "meta": { "total", "per_page", "current_page", "last_page" }, "links": { "first", "last", "prev", "next" } }
```

### Rate limiting
- FastAPI-Limiter applies in **production only**

## CLI commands

```bash
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py migrate:up       # Run Alembic migrations
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py migrate:down     # Rollback migration
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py migrate:status   # Migration status
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py queue:work       # Start RQ worker
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py cache:clear      # Clear Redis cache
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py secret           # Generate app secret
poetry run python3 ./src/cli.py v1:user:seed     # Seed test users
```

## Dev & production

```bash
poetry install
poetry run fastapi dev          # Development server (hot reload)
poetry run uvicorn main:app     # Production server
```

## Environment variables

```
APP_NAME, APP_SECRET, APP_PORT, APP_ENV, APP_LOCALE, APP_TIMEZONE
FRONTEND_URL
MEMORY_REDIS_HOST, MEMORY_REDIS_PORT, MEMORY_REDIS_PASSWORD
DATABASE_POSTGRE_URI, DATABASE_MONGO_URI
MAIL_URI
SWAGGER_TITLE, SWAGGER_DESCRIPTION, SWAGGER_VERSION
```

Config classes in `src/app/configs/` extend `AppConfig` base class.

## Testing

```bash
poetry run pytest -v                              # All tests (37 tests)
poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-report=html     # With coverage
poetry run pytest test/v1/test_user.py -v         # Single file
```

- `test/conftest.py` patches FastAPILimiter Redis to avoid connection errors
- `pytest.ini`: verbose, asyncio auto mode
- Default test user: `user@mail.com` / `12345678`

## Known issue: circular imports

`src/app/bases/app_realtime.py` ↔ `src/app/routes/app_ws_router.py` can circular-import.

**Fix:** use lazy import inside functions (e.g. `emitToUser`), never top-level cross-import between these two files.
